{"word":"H5594 - סָפַד - çâphad - saw-fad' - Lament","slug":"H5594","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סָפַד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>çâphad"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>saw-fad'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Lament"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E1;&#x05E4;&#x05D3; - sa&#x0302;phad</b> - <i>saw-fad'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>tear</i> the hair and <i>beat</i> the breasts (as Orientals do in grief); generally to <i>lament</i>; by implication to <i>wail: - </i>lament, mourn (-er), wail."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4553\">H4553</a>"}]}